{
  "texts": [
    "These instances underline the algorithm's proven capability to yield solutions across various problem settings, from engineering and power systems to emergency management, thereby validating its selection for our study on real-time robotic algorithms' WCET estimation.For the implementation of the GA in Python, this project utilizes the Optuna library [114], a next-generation hyperparameter optimization framework distinguished by its design criteria tailored for advanced hyperparameter optimization challenges.",
    "Optuna addresses several critical areas where traditional optimization frameworks exhibit limitations [114].",
    "Key features for Optuna are:• Define-by-Run API: A cornerstone feature of Optuna is its define-by-run API, which enhances construction of the parameter search space.",
    "Unlike traditional frameworks that require static definition, Optuna allows for dynamic construction, offering flexibility in complex models where optimal parameters and their ranges are not easily predetermined [114].",
    "This flexibility simplifies the coding process and enables more adaptive exploration of the search space, directly contributing to the optimization process's efficiency and effectiveness.• Efficient Optimization Strategies: Optuna incorporates efficient searching and pruning strategies, essential for navigating the search space effectively."
  ]
}